. Retrieved December 1, 2010.\n* [[Lee Stringer|Stringer, Lee]], [https://books.google.com/books?id=uX2Ol9BnT_gC&printsec=frontcover ''Grand Central Winter: Stories from the Street''], 1st ed., New York : Seven Stories Press, 1998. {{ISBN|1-888363-57-6}}\n* Szantos, Ruth [http://heinonline.org/HOL/LandingPage?handle=hein.journals/phnxlwrv4&div=21&id=&page=] Excuse Me- Can You Spare Some Change in This Economy- A Socio-Economic History of Anti-Panhandling Laws, 2010\n* Vissing, Yvonne [http://w3.salemstate.edu/~yvissing/ \"Out of Sight, Out of Mind: Homeless Children and Families in Small-Town America\"], 1996.\n* Vissing, Yvonne, [https://web.archive.org/web/20030422021059/http://www.forusa.org/Fellowship/Mar-Apr_03/Vissing.html \"The $ubtle War Against Children\", Fellowship], March/April 2003\n* Vladeck, Bruce, R., and the Committee on Health Care for Homeless People, Institute of Medicine, [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK218238/ \"Homelessness, Health, and Human needs\"], National Academies Press, 1988\n* Toth, Jennifer, ''The Mole People: Life in the Tunnels Beneath New York City'', 1993. {{ISBN|1-55652-190-1}}\n* [[United States Conference of Mayors]], [https://web.archive.org/web/20081230172249/http://www.usmayors.org/hungersurvey/2005/HH2005FINAL.pdf \"Hunger and Homelessness Survey\"], December 2005.\n* [[United States Department of Health and Human Services]], [http://aspe.hhs.gov/hsp/homelessness/strategies03/ \"Ending Chronic Homelessness: Strategies for Action\"], Report from the Secretary's Work Group on Ending Chronic Homelessness, March 2003.\n* [[University of Vermont]], [http://www.uvm.edu/~uvmpr/vq/VQFall02/Bed.html \"It starts With a Bed: UVM alums Richard Weintraub & Lyndia Downie lead fight to break cycle of homelessness in Boston], ''Vermont Quarterly'', Fall 2002.\n* U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development (2009). [https://web.archive.org/web/20121002214604/http://www.hudhre.info/documents/5thHomelessAssessmentReport.pdf 2009 Annual homeless assessment report to congress]. Washington, DC: U.S. Government Printing Office.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081011035440/http://www.usm.maine.edu/swo/faculty/david-wagner.html Wagner, David]. [https://books.google.com/books?id=lq1jpP57r_4C&printsec=frontcover Checkerboard Square: Culture and Resistance in a Homeless Community] (Boulder: Westview Press), 1993. {{ISBN|0-8133-1585-9}}\n* Ward, C. (2007). What they didn't teach us in library school; how the library became Heartbreak Hotel. TomDispatch.com. Retrieved from http://www.tomdispatch.com/post/174799/ward_how_the_public_library_became_heartbreak_hotel\n* Woolhouse, Megan, \"Homes for the holiday: Housing agency, nonprofit team up to help the homeless\", ''Boston Globe'', December 25, 2007.\n* Wortham, Jenna, [https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/13/technology/homeless-as-wi-fi-transmitters-creates-a-stir-in-austin.html \"Use of Homeless as Internet Hot Spots Backfires on Marketer\"], ''[[The New York Times]]'', March 12, 2012\n* Wright, James D., [https://books.google.com/books?id=LInRJu0O7mQC&printsec=frontcover \"Address Unknown: the homeless in America\"], New York : A. de Gruyter, Edition: 3, 1989\n* Kadi, J., & Ronald, R. (2016). Undermining housing affordability for New York's low-income households: The role of policy reform and rental sector restructuring. Critical Social Policy, 36(2): 265\u2013266. {{doi|10.1177/0261018315624172}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.nationalhomeless.org/ National Coalition for the Homeless]\n* [http://naeh.org/ National Alliance to End Homelessness]\n* [http://csh.org/ Corporation for Supportive Housing]\n* [http://www.nchv.org/ National Coalition for Homeless Veterans]\n* [http://www.nlihc.org/ National Low Income Housing Coalition]\n* [http://www.usich.gov/ U.S. Interagency Council on Homelessness \u2013 US Government]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050419011824/http://www.hud.gov/homeless/ United States Department of Housing and Urban Developm